Boosey & Hawkes marked up after H1 profits . Shares in UK instrument maker and music publisher Boosey & Hawkes Plc were marked over two percent higher on Tuesday after the company said first - half pretax profit rose 20 . 7 percent to a record 2 . 05 million stg . The shares were marked up 20p to 782 . 5p in an otherwise flat pre - market . No shares had changed hands by 0727 GMT . The company said turnover rose to 42 . 1 million stg in the first half from 40 . 5 million , with margins and operating profits moving ahead . Chief executive Richard Holland also said he was confident of further progress by the year - end . 
